I"<p>How hard can it be to do a drawing a day for 31 days? Actually.. it turned out to be quite a challenge I wonâ€™t lie.</p>

<p>Inktober is a challenge on <a href="https://www.instagram.com/inktober/" target="_blank">Instagram</a> by Jake Parker and has been going for a good few years.
<!--more--></p>

<p>Every October, artists all over the world take on the InkTober drawing challenge by doing one ink drawing a day the entire month.</p>

<h3 id="this-is-not-as-easy-as-it-looks">This is not as easy as it looks</h3>

<p>Things started well, with great enthusiasm each day. It started to become apparant after a while that fitting in a drawing when you have a job and kids.. and commitments.. etc was going to be hard.</p>

<p>Some of the days I was really pleased, others it was more keeping things going and as the days went on the thought of missing a day became unthinkable.</p>

<h3 id="you-made-it-good-job-buddy-">You made it! Good job buddy :)</h3>

<p>I managed the month, and it really inspired me to push on with my illustration and try and develop a style once and for all. Time to think of my own challenge to take me through to the new year.</p>

